And even one night when I was

00:19:02.876 --> 00:19:03.936 A:middle
working really late, and I

00:19:03.936 --> 00:19:05.366 A:middle
ordered a pizza, and the pizza

00:19:05.366 --> 00:19:07.566 A:middle
box said, "Our commitment is

00:19:07.566 --> 00:19:08.286 A:middle
quality."

00:19:09.076 --> 00:19:11.106 A:middle
[laughs] So I see the word

00:19:11.106 --> 00:19:12.346 A:middle
everywhere now.

00:19:12.446 --> 00:19:14.516 A:middle
It's really pervasive, from

00:19:14.636 --> 00:19:16.746 A:middle
signs to badges, to labels.

00:19:17.366 --> 00:19:19.246 A:middle
So I brought this up in a few of

00:19:19.246 --> 00:19:21.106 A:middle
the interviews, not because I

00:19:21.106 --> 00:19:22.236 A:middle
wanted to know what people

00:19:22.236 --> 00:19:23.866 A:middle
thought of labeling, but,

00:19:23.866 --> 00:19:26.886 A:middle
instead, to ask, why do we tend

00:19:26.886 --> 00:19:28.866 A:middle
to be drawn towards things that

00:19:28.866 --> 00:19:29.606 A:middle
are quality?

00:19:31.516 --> 00:19:34.066 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Well, survival instinct at

00:19:34.066 --> 00:19:34.556 A:middle
its root.

00:19:35.036 --> 00:19:36.536 A:middle
On a more deep level, I guess,

00:19:36.536 --> 00:19:37.806 A:middle
why do we desire quality?

00:19:38.296 --> 00:19:39.826 A:middle
We desire quality because we

00:19:39.826 --> 00:19:40.406 A:middle
want to live.

00:19:41.176 --> 00:19:44.096 A:middle
And a good survival strategy for

00:19:44.096 --> 00:19:47.626 A:middle
living is to put things into our

00:19:47.626 --> 00:19:50.296 A:middle
body, to eat things, or to wear

00:19:50.296 --> 00:19:52.066 A:middle
things, or to drive in things,

00:19:52.066 --> 00:19:54.396 A:middle
or to live in things that are

00:19:54.656 --> 00:19:56.936 A:middle
safe and have been well

00:19:56.936 --> 00:19:59.036 A:middle
constructed so they aren't going

00:19:59.036 --> 00:20:00.936 A:middle
to cause us bodily harm.

00:19:59.036 --> 00:20:00.936 A:middle
to cause us bodily harm.

00:20:01.616 --> 00:20:04.906 A:middle
And so I think purely on a

00:20:04.906 --> 00:20:07.236 A:middle
survival level, quality is a

00:20:07.236 --> 00:20:08.986 A:middle
very important concept for us.

00:20:08.986 --> 00:20:10.376 A:middle
It's a very important attribute

00:20:10.376 --> 00:20:11.666 A:middle
that we seek in everything.

00:20:14.256 --> 00:20:16.356 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Mike explained a bit further

00:20:16.356 --> 00:20:17.336 A:middle
during this interview.

00:20:17.746 --> 00:20:18.996 A:middle
We were talking about this

00:20:19.196 --> 00:20:22.356 A:middle
fictitious butcher shop, and if

00:20:22.356 --> 00:20:24.296 A:middle
we were in this shop, quality

00:20:24.296 --> 00:20:25.886 A:middle
would be communicated not only

00:20:25.886 --> 00:20:28.266 A:middle
by the products itself, but also

00:20:28.266 --> 00:20:30.706 A:middle
the shop being really clean and

00:20:30.706 --> 00:20:31.946 A:middle
interacting with the really nice

00:20:32.076 --> 00:20:33.146 A:middle
people that work there.

00:20:34.236 --> 00:20:36.246 A:middle
Every facet of the entire

00:20:36.246 --> 00:20:38.776 A:middle
experience would meet your

00:20:38.776 --> 00:20:40.436 A:middle
expectations, [laughs] and it

00:20:40.436 --> 00:20:42.506 A:middle
would also be connected to that

00:20:42.646 --> 00:20:44.216 A:middle
proposition of quality.

00:20:44.796 --> 00:20:48.266 A:middle
And that evokes trust.

00:20:49.546 --> 00:20:51.296 A:middle
Trust comes from products

00:20:51.366 --> 00:20:53.906 A:middle
upholding their promise, and

00:20:53.906 --> 00:20:56.046 A:middle
that quality experience is far

00:20:56.046 --> 00:20:57.956 A:middle
more important than any label

00:20:58.416 --> 00:21:00.046 A:middle
because I am definitely not

00:20:58.416 --> 00:21:00.046 A:middle
because I am definitely not

00:21:00.256 --> 00:21:02.986 A:middle
suggesting that you add a label

00:21:02.986 --> 00:21:04.996 A:middle
to your apps because you

00:21:04.996 --> 00:21:06.266 A:middle
[laughs] definitely don't need

00:21:06.886 --> 00:21:07.426 A:middle
to.

00:21:07.986 --> 00:21:10.046 A:middle
Every facet of your app

00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:12.496 A:middle
experience, from the screenshots

00:21:12.496 --> 00:21:14.006 A:middle
on the App Store to the

00:21:14.006 --> 00:21:16.596 A:middle
description, to how you respond

00:21:16.596 --> 00:21:19.196 A:middle
to customer reviews, all through

00:21:19.196 --> 00:21:21.716 A:middle
to your app's interface, these

00:21:21.716 --> 00:21:23.396 A:middle
experiences, these interactions

00:21:23.396 --> 00:21:25.296 A:middle
that you have with people, that

00:21:25.296 --> 00:21:27.566 A:middle
communicates the quality about

00:21:27.566 --> 00:21:28.996 A:middle
your app or your game.

00:21:29.936 --> 00:21:31.556 A:middle
And you don't want a label

00:21:31.556 --> 00:21:32.166 A:middle
anyway.

00:21:32.946 --> 00:21:33.316 A:middle
Why?

00:21:35.266 --> 00:21:37.436 A:middle
&gt;&gt; In a way, it's like saying

00:21:37.436 --> 00:21:38.226 A:middle
you're cool.

00:21:38.656 --> 00:21:41.476 A:middle
Like, being cool doesn't involve

00:21:41.806 --> 00:21:42.786 A:middle
saying you're cool.

00:21:43.326 --> 00:21:46.396 A:middle
[laughs] And, you know, you only

00:21:46.476 --> 00:21:48.096 A:middle
say that someone else is cool.

00:21:48.096 --> 00:21:49.986 A:middle
It's only something which can be

00:21:49.986 --> 00:21:51.626 A:middle
sort of determined by an outside

00:21:51.626 --> 00:21:52.486 A:middle
party, in a way.

00:21:53.656 --> 00:21:56.146 A:middle
And even then, there's a certain

00:21:56.146 --> 00:21:57.196 A:middle
context where it feels more

00:21:57.196 --> 00:21:58.316 A:middle
appropriate than others.

00:21:58.316 --> 00:21:59.396 A:middle
Like, if we're talking about

00:21:59.816 --> 00:22:01.976 A:middle
Thelonious Monk and we're just

00:21:59.816 --> 00:22:01.976 A:middle
Thelonious Monk and we're just

00:22:01.976 --> 00:22:03.576 A:middle
talking about jazz in the '50's,

00:22:03.676 --> 00:22:04.806 A:middle
like, that's cool.

00:22:05.066 --> 00:22:06.546 A:middle
That's the birth of cool, right.

00:22:06.546 --> 00:22:08.476 A:middle
[laughs] That's where it's,

00:22:08.476 --> 00:22:10.296 A:middle
like, totally appropriate to use

00:22:10.296 --> 00:22:13.586 A:middle
that kind of term, but that's an

00:22:13.586 --> 00:22:14.776 A:middle
earned coolness.

00:22:15.066 --> 00:22:17.146 A:middle
And so quality has to be earned.

00:22:17.756 --> 00:22:19.926 A:middle
&gt;&gt; I think Mike makes a really

00:22:19.926 --> 00:22:20.386 A:middle
good point.

00:22:20.916 --> 00:22:24.126 A:middle
So the significance of quality

00:22:24.126 --> 00:22:24.916 A:middle
is massive.

00:22:25.086 --> 00:22:27.416 A:middle
As we heard, it impacts our

00:22:27.466 --> 00:22:30.356 A:middle
every day, it can be felt, and

00:22:30.416 --> 00:22:32.306 A:middle
it evokes trust in the people

00:22:32.306 --> 00:22:33.906 A:middle
that are using your app.

00:22:35.196 --> 00:22:35.686 A:middle
All right.

00:22:37.106 --> 00:22:39.046 A:middle
Now, everyone I talked to

00:22:39.106 --> 00:22:39.996 A:middle
throughout these interviews,

00:22:40.076 --> 00:22:42.066 A:middle
they all have a passion for

00:22:42.066 --> 00:22:43.986 A:middle
excellence, so we're going to

00:22:43.986 --> 00:22:45.606 A:middle
talk about four design

00:22:45.866 --> 00:22:47.706 A:middle
aspirations, and these four

00:22:47.706 --> 00:22:49.366 A:middle
aspirations really stood out to

00:22:49.366 --> 00:22:51.116 A:middle
me because, well, they seemed

00:22:51.116 --> 00:22:53.306 A:middle
just so incredibly elusive and

00:22:53.306 --> 00:22:54.186 A:middle
hard to achieve.

00:22:54.686 --> 00:22:57.776 A:middle
But these designers use them as

00:22:57.776 --> 00:23:00.046 A:middle
motivation to strive for quality

00:22:57.776 --> 00:23:00.046 A:middle
motivation to strive for quality

00:23:00.046 --> 00:23:01.866 A:middle
in their work, and these

00:23:01.866 --> 00:23:04.116 A:middle
aspirations are to design things

00:23:04.376 --> 00:23:07.846 A:middle
that are simple, stunning,

00:23:09.436 --> 00:23:12.746 A:middle
timeless, and leave a positive

00:23:12.746 --> 00:23:13.916 A:middle
impact on people's lives.

00:23:14.996 --> 00:23:16.326 A:middle
So we're going to dig into each

00:23:16.366 --> 00:23:18.246 A:middle
one of these to discover why

00:23:18.246 --> 00:23:20.536 A:middle
they're important and also how

00:23:20.536 --> 00:23:22.066 A:middle
they provide motivation to

00:23:22.066 --> 00:23:23.236 A:middle
create great design.

00:23:24.916 --> 00:23:25.246 A:middle
All right.

00:23:25.876 --> 00:23:27.586 A:middle
Let's start with simplicity.

00:23:27.846 --> 00:23:30.846 A:middle
This came up in response to this

00:23:30.896 --> 00:23:33.306 A:middle
question: What makes a great

00:23:33.376 --> 00:23:33.576 A:middle
app?

00:23:35.446 --> 00:23:36.206 A:middle
&gt;&gt; It's simple.

00:23:36.596 --> 00:23:38.566 A:middle
It doesn't try to do more than

00:23:38.566 --> 00:23:39.466 A:middle
it needs to do.

00:23:39.866 --> 00:23:40.996 A:middle
And what it does, it does it

00:23:41.066 --> 00:23:41.676 A:middle
really well.

00:23:41.676 --> 00:23:44.226 A:middle
&gt;&gt; I don't know about you, but I

00:23:44.226 --> 00:23:45.696 A:middle
have heard that a lot.

00:23:46.546 --> 00:23:47.896 A:middle
[laughs] So I'm sure you've

00:23:47.896 --> 00:23:48.846 A:middle
heard it before too.

00:23:49.346 --> 00:23:51.246 A:middle
But there's got to be a reason

00:23:51.246 --> 00:23:53.206 A:middle
why that phrase is on repeat,

00:23:53.926 --> 00:23:56.036 A:middle
and I was really thinking about

00:23:56.036 --> 00:23:57.166 A:middle
this after the interview.

00:23:57.166 --> 00:23:59.686 A:middle
You know, why should apps be

00:23:59.686 --> 00:24:01.106 A:middle
simple, and why is that a good

00:23:59.686 --> 00:24:01.106 A:middle
simple, and why is that a good

00:24:01.106 --> 00:24:01.476 A:middle
thing?

00:24:02.276 --> 00:24:03.926 A:middle
Well, it finally clicked for me

00:24:03.926 --> 00:24:05.176 A:middle
one day after work.

00:24:06.326 --> 00:24:08.006 A:middle
I got home, I needed to cook

00:24:08.006 --> 00:24:09.736 A:middle
some dinner, and I needed an app

00:24:10.026 --> 00:24:11.856 A:middle
to help me with a recipe, to not

00:24:11.856 --> 00:24:13.306 A:middle
make cooking any harder than it

00:24:13.306 --> 00:24:13.966 A:middle
already is.

00:24:14.566 --> 00:24:15.806 A:middle
And as soon as I was home, I

00:24:16.066 --> 00:24:18.156 A:middle
remembered that I needed to go

00:24:18.156 --> 00:24:20.166 A:middle
ahead and put, book pet care for

00:24:20.166 --> 00:24:21.936 A:middle
my two dogs because I'm going on

00:24:21.936 --> 00:24:22.846 A:middle
vacation after WWDC.

00:24:22.846 --> 00:24:23.786 A:middle
Aw, aren't they cute?

00:24:24.736 --> 00:24:28.176 A:middle
[laughs] Okay, we have to stop

00:24:28.176 --> 00:24:29.066 A:middle
before I get distracted.

00:24:29.066 --> 00:24:31.136 A:middle
We're talking about two tasks

00:24:31.476 --> 00:24:34.176 A:middle
here, cooking dinner and pet

00:24:34.246 --> 00:24:34.476 A:middle
care.

00:24:35.636 --> 00:24:36.906 A:middle
Why do the apps that help me

00:24:36.906 --> 00:24:38.166 A:middle
with those, why do they need to

00:24:38.166 --> 00:24:38.826 A:middle
be simple?

00:24:38.876 --> 00:24:41.546 A:middle
Well, it's because I don't go

00:24:41.546 --> 00:24:43.746 A:middle
into them all the time, so they

00:24:43.746 --> 00:24:44.886 A:middle
need to be instantly

00:24:44.886 --> 00:24:46.546 A:middle
understandable, as if I already

00:24:46.546 --> 00:24:47.526 A:middle
know how to use them.

00:24:47.996 --> 00:24:49.556 A:middle
So familiar navigation and

00:24:49.556 --> 00:24:50.616 A:middle
gestures really help with that.

00:24:51.616 --> 00:24:53.196 A:middle
You know, the goal is launch the

00:24:53.196 --> 00:24:55.536 A:middle
app, I totally get it, and I can

00:24:55.536 --> 00:24:56.466 A:middle
get the task done.

00:24:57.466 --> 00:24:58.766 A:middle
But why else should they be

00:24:58.766 --> 00:24:59.206 A:middle
simple?

00:25:00.286 --> 00:25:02.696 A:middle
Well, it could be a good day or

00:25:02.696 --> 00:25:04.626 A:middle
a bad day, but I'm using these

00:25:04.626 --> 00:25:07.266 A:middle
apps in real life, and that's

00:25:07.266 --> 00:25:08.526 A:middle
where all of my mental energy

00:25:08.526 --> 00:25:10.666 A:middle
should be, not wasted on a

00:25:10.666 --> 00:25:13.066 A:middle
confusing app UI, interaction,

00:25:13.296 --> 00:25:14.086 A:middle
or interface.

00:25:14.756 --> 00:25:17.116 A:middle
Apps should not be a burden, and

00:25:17.116 --> 00:25:18.696 A:middle
it's a lot easier to get back to

00:25:18.696 --> 00:25:20.126 A:middle
real life when they're simple.

00:25:21.086 --> 00:25:22.986 A:middle
So how would you describe

00:25:23.046 --> 00:25:25.016 A:middle
simplicity in apps and games?

00:25:25.096 --> 00:25:27.986 A:middle
&gt;&gt; It just has to work.

00:25:28.086 --> 00:25:31.056 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Right. It just has to work

00:25:31.056 --> 00:25:32.346 A:middle
for the people that are using

00:25:32.346 --> 00:25:32.636 A:middle
it.

00:25:32.916 --> 00:25:34.056 A:middle
But there's actually something

00:25:34.056 --> 00:25:34.636 A:middle
else here.

00:25:35.636 --> 00:25:36.876 A:middle
You don't want people to feel

00:25:36.876 --> 00:25:37.806 A:middle
distracted.

00:25:38.346 --> 00:25:40.756 A:middle
Simple, easy-to-understand apps

00:25:41.086 --> 00:25:43.096 A:middle
that just work, well, they help

00:25:43.136 --> 00:25:44.276 A:middle
keep people focused.

00:25:45.236 --> 00:25:46.566 A:middle
I know for me, I can get really

00:25:46.566 --> 00:25:47.776 A:middle
easily overwhelmed if

00:25:47.846 --> 00:25:49.236 A:middle
something's out of place.

00:25:49.276 --> 00:25:50.446 A:middle
It can just take me out of that

00:25:50.446 --> 00:25:52.246 A:middle
experience, and that makes

00:25:52.316 --> 00:25:53.956 A:middle
getting the task done even

00:25:53.956 --> 00:25:54.426 A:middle
harder.

00:25:54.426 --> 00:25:56.466 A:middle
I was actually talking to Jessie

00:25:56.466 --> 00:25:58.706 A:middle
about this, and I asked her,

00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:00.806 A:middle
what does she look for in great

00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:00.806 A:middle
what does she look for in great

00:26:01.006 --> 00:26:01.326 A:middle
apps?

00:26:01.866 --> 00:26:04.246 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Make my life feel a little

00:26:04.246 --> 00:26:06.396 A:middle
bit easier or make my life feel

00:26:06.396 --> 00:26:08.026 A:middle
a little bit nicer or more

00:26:08.026 --> 00:26:08.816 A:middle
luxurious.

00:26:09.616 --> 00:26:11.566 A:middle
&gt;&gt; I think that is just spot on.

00:26:12.236 --> 00:26:13.946 A:middle
Make my life feel a little bit

00:26:13.946 --> 00:26:17.166 A:middle
easier by being simple, focused,

00:26:18.096 --> 00:26:20.086 A:middle
instantly understandable, and

00:26:20.086 --> 00:26:22.936 A:middle
just do one thing really, really

00:26:22.936 --> 00:26:23.076 A:middle
well.

00:26:23.996 --> 00:26:24.926 A:middle
That is the goal.

00:26:25.396 --> 00:26:29.206 A:middle
All right, this next aspiration

00:26:29.206 --> 00:26:31.676 A:middle
is to be stunning, and this came

00:26:31.676 --> 00:26:32.716 A:middle
up when I was talking to

00:26:32.836 --> 00:26:33.406 A:middle
Caroline.

00:26:33.816 --> 00:26:36.626 A:middle
I asked her, "What communicates

00:26:36.936 --> 00:26:38.466 A:middle
great visual design?"

00:26:39.166 --> 00:26:41.786 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Just that polish.

00:26:42.206 --> 00:26:43.646 A:middle
Does it look great?

00:26:43.646 --> 00:26:44.866 A:middle
Does it look stunning?

00:26:45.406 --> 00:26:46.826 A:middle
And then, the other level of

00:26:46.826 --> 00:26:48.926 A:middle
polish, on a different kind of

00:26:48.926 --> 00:26:50.516 A:middle
app, like a game or something,

00:26:50.516 --> 00:26:52.716 A:middle
to me is making it feel

00:26:52.836 --> 00:26:54.806 A:middle
beautiful as an experience, like

00:26:54.806 --> 00:26:56.296 A:middle
it feels like a work of art.

00:26:57.626 --> 00:26:58.666 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Right, yes.

00:26:59.436 --> 00:27:00.476 A:middle
So we talked a little bit

00:26:59.436 --> 00:27:00.476 A:middle
So we talked a little bit

00:27:00.476 --> 00:27:02.536 A:middle
further about this, and Caroline

00:27:02.536 --> 00:27:04.656 A:middle
explained that what she means by

00:27:04.806 --> 00:27:07.636 A:middle
polish is things lining up just

00:27:07.716 --> 00:27:08.986 A:middle
the way you intend them to be,

00:27:09.506 --> 00:27:10.956 A:middle
including how it feels.

